	<LocalizedText>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Pontic Scythia</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_FULLNAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Scythians of the Pontic Steppe</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_ADJECTIVE" Language="en_US"><Text>Scythian</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>Nomadic Iranian-speaking peoples who dominated the Pontic-Caspian steppe, including much of present-day southern Ukraine, during the first millennium BCE.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_ABILITY_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Riders of the Pontic Steppe</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_PONTIC_SCYTHIA_ABILITY_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>Design target: cavalry mobility, horse-resource starts, and kurgan culture. V0.1 is a playable shell pending custom modifier testing.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_LOADING_CIV_INTRO_TEXT_PONTIC_SCYTHIA" Language="en_US"><Text>Across the open steppe north of the Black Sea, Scythian power moved with horse, bow, and trade.</Text></Row>

		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_KYIVAN_RUS_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Kyivan Rus'</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_KYIVAN_RUS_FULLNAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Kyivan Rus'</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_KYIVAN_RUS_ADJECTIVE" Language="en_US"><Text>Rus'</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_KYIVAN_RUS_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>A medieval polity centered on Kyiv, tied to river commerce, Orthodox Christianity, urban law, and diplomacy across Eastern Europe.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_KYIVAN_RUS_ABILITY_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Route from the Varangians</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_KYIVAN_RUS_ABILITY_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>Design target: river trade, culture from diplomacy, and defensive city networks. V0.1 is a playable shell pending custom modifier testing.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_LOADING_CIV_INTRO_TEXT_KYIVAN_RUS" Language="en_US"><Text>From Kyiv, river routes carried law, faith, trade, and power between the Baltic, Black Sea, and steppe.</Text></Row>

		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_UKRAINE_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Ukraine</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_UKRAINE_FULLNAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Ukraine</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_UKRAINE_ADJECTIVE" Language="en_US"><Text>Ukrainian</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_CIVILIZATION_UKRAINE_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>A modern nation rooted in Black Sea and steppe histories, Kyivan urban traditions, Cossack self-government, agricultural wealth, civic resilience, and state sovereignty.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_UKRAINE_ABILITY_NAME" Language="en_US"><Text>Breadbasket and Bastion</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_TRAIT_UKRAINE_ABILITY_DESCRIPTION" Language="en_US"><Text>Design target: food and gold from fertile farms, production while repairing or defending, and strong rail-era industry. V0.1 is a playable shell pending custom modifier testing.</Text></Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_LOADING_CIV_INTRO_TEXT_UKRAINE" Language="en_US"><Text>From fertile black earth to industrial cities, Ukraine endures through harvest, culture, and civic defense.</Text></Row>

